		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I understand, but really, I doubt you'll find someone who wants to do all the crap work (tedious, monotonous programming and the like). A port wouldn't really have to take years. I think if I were -really- committed to my project, working on it every day, I could really progress a lot. But sometimes the crap work seems too crappy and I don't want to do it, so I just do something else.
<br />
<br />I really recommend learning how to program for the NES though. While figuring this MM9 stuff out, you could at the same time be educating yourself to program for the NES, so if it turns out that no one here will do the work, you'll have a better shot at doing it yourself. Also, this is a very helpful community, so it's really unlikely you'll be hopelessly stuck. And plus, it's fun to have that knowledge, knowing that you could do lots of stuff with it.

		

